title: Independent candidate Muhammad Atif wins NA-22 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Muhammad Atif has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-22 Mardan-II securing 1,14,748 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party’s Amir Haider Azam Khan candidate, who bagged 66,159 votes.
The voters’ turnout remained 39 percent.
